                    <abstract lang="eng">While the well-established Prandtl-Tomlinson (PT) model of atomic friction predicts that the friction force decreases with temperature and grows with velocity, several recent experiments reported that a nonmonotonic temperature dependence and a decreasing velocity dependence may also occur. We propose a minimal extension of the PT model, incorporating the possibility of thermally activated contact strengthening and providing one common framework to quantitatively explain all those &quot;anomalous&apos;&apos; experimental findings, as well as the previously known &quot;normal&apos;&apos; (PT-like) behavior.</abstract>
